title: Cloak golden gate — obliterated message loses
story: cloak-of-darkness
description: Three dark entries obliterate the message (first-time →
  trampled, third-time → obliterated, per the stumble rule's ordinal
  blocks); reading it obliterated is the lose ending. The second dark
  entry stumbles without changing state. ADR-210 AC-1 golden gate
  (frozen 2026-07-10).

---

# Dark entry 1: message goes to trampled
> south
[OK: contains "Blundering around in the dark isn't a good idea!"]

> north
[OK: contains "Foyer of the Opera House"]

# Dark entry 2: stumble fires, no state change
> south
[OK: contains "Blundering around in the dark isn't a good idea!"]

> north
[OK: contains "Foyer of the Opera House"]

# Dark entry 3: message goes to obliterated
> south
[OK: contains "Blundering around in the dark isn't a good idea!"]

> north
[OK: contains "Foyer of the Opera House"]

# Hang up the cloak and return to the lit bar
> west
[OK: contains "Cloakroom"]

> remove cloak
[OK: contains "You take off the velvet cloak"]

> hang cloak on hook
[OK: contains "put the velvet cloak on the brass hook"]

> east
[OK: contains "Foyer of the Opera House"]

> south
[OK: contains "Foyer Bar"]

# Obliterated message: the lose phrase and the defeat event
> read message
[OK: contains "trampled beyond recognition"]
[OK: contains "You have lost"]
[EVENT: true, type="story.defeat"]
